parameters:
This is the castle town of Edo. It's vast, so make sure not
to get lost.
I want to go home, but it's half-destroyed, what a mess...

Hehehe... There's nothing like drinking sake in the middle
of the day.

Seeing the demon sobered me up completely. The castle's gone
up in flames too, what to do now...

[Sign] If you're lost on where to go, come this way--The
Fortune-Teller with a High Success Rate

Are you planning to go fight those demons? Can't be helped,
I guess. I won't run away either; I'll keep my wares
available. What do you need?

Thanks. I'll be here anytime, so come by when you need
something.

(First, I should go to the polisher at Nihonbashi and have
my treasured sword sharpened.)

It's hardly the time for business. Everyone is too scared
and has shut themselves in at home.

Come one, come all! Today's newspaper is here! It features
an article about Nezumi Komachi distributing the coins she
stole! Buy your newspaper now~!

(... Mufufu. My exploits are perfectly captured in the
newspaper! I wonder which wealthy mansion I should sneak
into next.)

Nezumi Komachi has infiltrated the Tomitakaya-san's mansion!
She stole a lot of koban and scattered them all over Edo!

(The Tomitakaya mansion... it was incredibly spacious. Such
a luxurious estate, one could never enter in a lifetime
without resorting to theft.)

Extra, extra! It seems the bandit gang from Kamitai Village
has been caught!

(The people of Kamitai Village can finally return to their
peaceful lives. I couldn't steal as a phantom thief, but
making the world a better place isn't too bad either.)

Nezumi Komachi has set her sights on the lord's mansion! The
details are written in the town bulletin!

Ever since Nezumi Komachi stopped making headlines, the
newsletters just aren't selling... I wonder where Nezumi
Komachi has gone off to...

(...I promised the authorities I wouldn't steal in Edo
anymore, so there's nothing I can do... I'm sorry.)

The bandits of Suranashi Village have been captured! For
more details, check the town bulletin!

(I'm glad I was able to infiltrate the bandit fortress and
return safely. One wrong step and I might have spent my
whole life in that fortress...)

I heard there was an incident in the red-light district, do
you know anything about it? The courtesans all seem tight-
lipped...

Well... I really don't know anything about the red-light
district... I'm just an ordinary town girl, so...

A new fox teahouse has opened in Ueno! The delicious Nanban-
style sweets are super popular!

(That must be Masaki-chan's shop. It's amazing that it's
already made it into the newspaper articles.)

I've heard rumors about a demon appearing in Atami... but I
wonder if it's true. It would be quite the problem if we
published an article in the town bulletin and it turned out
to be wrong...

(It seems that the rumors of the demon are gradually
spreading to Edo as well... It looks like we have no choice
but to proceed with the demon extermination as secretly as
possible.)

It's a major incident! The castle tower in Edo is ablaze!
Mount Fuji looks like it's about to erupt too, what a
disaster!

(...I wonder if the news bulletins will sell when there's no
one left in Edo? No, no, before I worry about that, I need
to make sure I do what I must--)

Today, Edo is blessed with clear weather again. Even though
it's autumn, it's still warm.

Lately, things have become somewhat dangerous, haven't
they...

--! That's right. Before I leave Edo, I should stop by the
dumpling shop. I have to tell Oei-san that I'm heading out
to Suranashi Village, or else I'll make her worry like last
time.

Welcome to the fortune-telling booth! I will divine your
path\c[17]Currently on \V[60] Chapter\c[0]

Go to the kimono shop Tomitakaya in Nihonbashi. It's good
luck to meet with Tomitakaya at Oei's dango shop and then
head to Tomitakaya's residence afterward

Talk with Omitsu-chan at the dango shop. Have a conversation
with the old woman on the bridge in Fukagawa. Rescue the
pharmacist at the well in Asakusa. Obtain the Recollection
Shack from the Straw Millionaire event starting in Shinjuku

If you accomplish all of the above, the village chief will
come to Oei's dango shop, so it would be good to head to
Kami-Tai Village from there.

After going to the dango shop, defeat the Kokuyou Tengu in
Yotsuya. Talk with Omitsu-chan in the temple hut. Help the
fox at the sideshow in Nihonbashi

After completing all three tasks above, listen to the story
from the town crier in the castle town and then it's good
luck to head to the Kiritodo residence in Hibiya

Defeat the exile leader and his underlings who come to your
home (becoming submissive triggers an event with the exile
leader). Talk with the village chief at the stone monument
in the western island. Have a conversation at Kachou's house
and go to Kisanosuke's house to receive a fishing rod

Catch a tuna at the southern beach, and listen to
Kisanosuke's story about the white-haired monk. Meeting the
white-haired monk and catching at least five sea bream as
requested will advance the story.

After going to the dango shop, talk with the town crier in
the castle town. Receive a night hawk's mat from Yugiri-chan
at the ninja mansion in Marunouchi. Become a night hawk and
talk to over 20 clients during the night (H events can be
triggered by choosing 'Refuse')

Afterward, when an incident occurs in the castle town at
night, chase after the culprit towards Yotsuya for good
luck. If Yugiri-chan joins your party, don't forget to
change her equipment to stronger armor and accessories.

Talk with all the lecherous men in Sunuramu Village once (H
events do not need to be triggered). Reunite with Yugiri-
chan near the village chief's house and then heading
straight to the bandit fort will progress the story.

Catch a softshell turtle while fishing in Ueno and give it
to Tiger Masamune in Asakusa.. After hearing about an
introduction letter at night in the red-light district, talk
with Oei-san. After obtaining the introduction letter, go to
Momiji-san's house in the red-light district. Take on
clients more than 15 times in the red-light district

(H events in the red-light district can be avoided by
choosing 'Refuse') Then, encountering a criminal while
changing into a courtesan's clothes in the red-light
district will progress the story for good luck. If Momiji-
san joins your party, don't forget to upgrade her equipment
with stronger armor and accessories.

If you go to the hot spring inn in Atami, I believe your
story will progress. The weapon shop in Atami sells powerful
weapons and armor, so be sure to purchase them.

Go to the performance hall in Nihonbashi and act as a stand-
in on stage. Work at the fox teahouse in Ueno and then
receive a pass from the magistrate's office. After
retrieving your pass in Yotsuya, head towards the checkpoint
east of Fukagawa. Don't forget to strengthen Masaki-san's
equipment once she joins your party.

Give a rusty sword to the polisher in Nihonbashi. Going to
Momiji-san's residence in the red-light district at night
and finding a letter will progress your story.

After retrieving your sword from the polisher, please
proceed from Marunouchi to the castle! Good luck!

Oh dear... It's sad that as a fortune-teller, I couldn't
foresee my own shop burning down... There is nothing more
for me to tell you. Please head towards Mount Fuji, the
demon's stronghold. Wishing you a good ending--
I cannot tell fortunes without money. Please prepare 50 mon.

Oh my, that's unfortunate. If you're ever lost again, please
come back.

Fueee... It's so sad that as a fortune-teller, I couldn't
foresee my own shop burning down... There's nothing more to
tell you. Please head to Mount Fuji, the stronghold of the
demons. Wishing you a good outcome--
From here to the west is the Hibiya Daimyo's mansion.

It's come to this... Is Edo beyond saving now? Maybe I
should prepare to go back to the countryside...

I wonder what kind of woman the Phantom Thief Nezumi Komachi
is? I'd love to meet her just once.
I heard there was a bizarre incident... It's scary.
Hmm...? There's a crowd gathering. I wonder what happened?

--Extra, extra! It seems that Nezumi Komachi has been
caught!
What?! Really?! Nezumi Komachi has been caught?!

Yes! Last night, she was caught breaking into the Kiridou
family's daimyo mansion by Lord Kiridou Gamen himself! It's
information straight from the source!
~~~~! (It can't be! A fake me? Or maybe...!)

They say they're going to publicly display the captured
Nezumi Komachi in front of the Hibiya mansion as an example,
for causing such a stir in Edo.
...! (I must hurry to Hibiya and see for myself!)

It seems they're going to publicly display the captured
Nezumi Komachi in front of the Hibiya mansion as an example,
branding her as a notorious villain who caused an uproar in
Edo.
Extra! Extra! Another courtesan has been murdered!

Already five people have gone missing or been killed this
month. Knock on wood...

Ever since Nezumi Komachi stopped showing up, things have
gotten dangerous... But what could have happened to Nezumi
Komachi?
...! (A courtesan was killed...? Could it be...)

(Could it really be the work of a demon...? If that's the
case, I must fight, or more victims will fall...)

(I should go to the ninja mansion in Marunouchi to meet with
Yugiri-chan.)

"They say the night hawk's body was covered in bite marks
and all the flesh had been eaten. You better be careful not
to wander around at night, young lady."
For real? So you finally got caught...
Hueee... Isn't this a bizarre incident...
Give me the newspaper, give me the newspaper!
Give me the newspaper, the newspaper!

Yotaka are prostitutes who sell their bodies individually at
night. Unlike brothels, they're always alone, so it's easy
for them to encounter danger if they come across a dangerous
man.

Welcome. This is a tool shop. We also buy items, so if you
have something you want to sell, don't hesitate to sell it
to us.

...Oops, where are you going? You've just sold your
virginity, so running away after selling is not allowed.

No joke at all--you've already agreed to sell your virginity
to me and received 10,000 mon in cash. The transaction is
complete. If you run away, I'll take it to the magistrate.

...I'm sorry. I was about to sell something very important
for the sake of money...

...It's troublesome for me too when you lie twice. You need
to sell it properly.
...I'll ask one more time, will you sell your virginity?

If you're truly sorry, then good. Virginity is something
precious. Young ladies shouldn't sell it off so easily...
And there won't be a second refund, okay?

Yes. You are absolutely right. I won't sell my virginity
again, even as a joke. I'm really sorry...
--Karin bowed her head and returned the 10,000 mon.

\c[27]Number of actual performances +1, vaginal ejaculation +1,
lewdness +3\c[0]
I'm on my way to the castle. Make way.
(...Let's head to the dumpling shop first.)
Hey, Karin-chan. You always seem so cheerful
Hello, Landlord. Thank you for always taking care of me.
By the way, this month's rent hasn't been paid yet...

----! (Oh no! I've carelessly thrown away all the stolen
money, now I don't have any... What should I do...!?)

Oh, you seem to be out of cash? Don't worry about it. Your
father has paid a lot already, so there's no need to rush.
It's fine as long as you pay within the year.
I'm... I'm sorry for taking advantage of your kindness...

It's been five years since your father, Nakatarou-san,
disappeared. Still no word from him, huh?

Yes... not a single clue... I also don't understand why my
father disappeared...

Ah, I'm sorry. Anyway, don't worry about the rent. Just pay
it when you have the money, okay?
Yes... Thank you very much, Landlord.

Even so, Nezumi Komachi is amazing, huh She's already
broken into about eight wealthy homes and still hasn't been
caught. True to her name, she must be really nimble.

Good morning, Karin-chan. Have you heard? It seems that
Nezumi Komachi has broken into the Tomichouya's mansion.
That makes it her ninth successful heist. What an incredible
thief she is.
Uh-uhm. What to do. What to do...

Huh? Landlord, what's the matter? Is there something
troubling you?

Ah, is that you, Karin-chan? You see, it seems my great-
uncle is critically ill. I want to rush over there right
away, but...

Yes. But with an old man's legs like mine, I won't make it
in time. If only I could ride a horse, I could get there
quickly...

I just happened to have acquired a horse; would you like to
use it?
--Eh?! Really? Karin-chan, you're a horse owner?

Yes. It's old but I think it can still run just fine. I'll
bring it over now--

Oh! Thank you, Karin-chan! This is just what I needed. I'll
borrow this horse then.

Ahaha! It seems more spirited than before. You really wanted
to keep running in your prime, didn't you?

Yeah! Alright, the horse looks energetic and that's great.
With this, I should be able to get to my relative's house in
no time. As thanks, feel free to use this hut as you like!
Really? Thank you so much, Landlord! Please take care--
\c[17]Karin Obtained The [Recollection Hut] From The Straw!\c[0]
--Karin Obtained The [Recollection Hut] From The Straw!

The fortune teller over there is amazing. She pinpointed the
location of my lost hairpin in one go.

I've decided not to go out at night because it's scary. The
culprit hasn't been caught, so you be careful too.

I came to buy some dumplings for grandpa's errand. You're
such a good girl, Omitsu-chan.

Ehehe. Grandpa and I both love Oei-san's dumplings! Please
give me 10 mitarashi dumplings.

Ahaha! You say the nicest things Alright, I'll throw in an
extra one for you.
Omitsu-chan, is the temple school fun?

Yes! I've made lots of friends. Come and play at the temple
school sometime, Karin-oneechan

She's such a cute kid. Despite being the granddaughter of a
well-to-do samurai family, she attends a commoner's temple
school; her grandpa is quite a stylish man.

Yes. They have a home in Marunouchi. She says our dumplings
are the best in Edo, which really makes me proud. Haha!

Hey, Oei-san. Aren't you going back inside the shop yet? I'd
like to place an order.

Oops, my bad! Karin, if you have time, could you help out at
the dumpling shop?
--Oei is chatting and laughing with Omitsu.
(The bustling noise of a lively crowd...)

...hmm? There's a lively voice coming from the direction of
the dango shop. Let's go check it out.
Yes, here's your favorite, old man: three skewers of dango.
Ha ha ha! I am most grateful. Now, Kanemaru, eat up.

Wow! Delicious! I like these even more than the dango we got
as souvenirs; they're so soft

I'm glad to see you enjoying them so much\I[15] I also
recommend our shop's special strawberry daifuku.

Please, help yourself. But be careful not to eat too hastily
and choke.
Wow! So much!? Thank you very much

Seeing my son so happy makes me glad I brought him along.
Sorry for reserving the whole shop, Oei.

Don't mention it. It's my way of returning the favor for
that golden badge you gave me last time. Today everything is
on the house, so please eat as much as you like, old man.
Ah, big sister Karin, good morning

Ah, Karin. You've appeared at just the right moment. I was
about to send a messenger to your house.
Whoa--!? Uh... Lord...! Why are you at the shop again...!?

No, old man! If you were going to come to the shop, you
should have told me in advance...! You surprised me!

I apologize for the sudden visit, Karin, the poster girl of
the dango shop. I haven't inspected Edo in a while, so I
decided to stop by. It's a good opportunity since my son is
with me today as well.
Lady Karin. I had fun playing kemari with you the other day

Lord Kanemaru is also at the shop...? No, really, it was
such a surprise.

Ah, Yugiri has arrived too. Come up to the parlor. Let's
enjoy some dango together.

Ngh--!? Ugh...! Ughhh...!? (Why is His Lordship here--!? And
Lord Kanemaru too!? )

I asked Masane to tell you to come to the dango shop as
well. Kanemaru, I want to talk with Karin and Yugiri for a
bit. You should go see how Oei and Omitsu work in the
kitchen. Everything is a learning experience.

--Kanemaru left the parlor and headed towards where Oei and
Omitsu were working.

I wanted to talk with the three of you. Having tea and dango
while we chat isn't a bad idea.

Thump thump... (I've done guard duty before, but this is my
first conversation with His Lordship. Ugh... I'm so
nervous...)

...Your Lordship, do you enjoy walking around town dressed
as a retiree?

A long time ago, my great-uncle, who was then Shogun,
climbed up to the castle tower and was advised by his
retainers to use a telescope. He refused, reasoning that if
the Shogun was seen peering into the town with a telescope
from the tower, it would be unpleasant for the townspeople.

Therefore, once a month I disguise myself as a retiree and
inspect Edo. You both did well on your recent mission to
Atami to subdue the demons. It was hard work indeed--

I've received reports from Elder Masane. Just to confirm,
it's true that in Atami demons were leading an army,
correct?

Yes... They were armed and called themselves the Oni En
Party.

Until now, the demons were only small groups, but this time
it was different. Without help, both of us might have been
captured by the demons and our lives endangered...

As you both have reported, demons forming an army is indeed
a threat. I will gather 1000 soldiers each at Edo Castle and
the Sagami garrison. From now on, the Hatamoto should come
to the castle armed. This should reduce the burden on the
Iga ninja group.
Ah... Thank you very much! That's a great help!

Yugiri, I've heard about your past from Masane. You
volunteered to join the Iga ninja after your family was
killed by demons in your hometown, right?

Yes... I am from Koshu, which was once governed by your
Lordship. After suffering the calamity of a demon attack,
thanks to Lady Masane's efforts, I was able to join the Iga
ninja of Edo and become who I am today.

Hmm. I think it commendable that you took over as head of
the Iga ninja group six months ago, even though your master
Hanzo was killed by demons. I want you to continue working
hard for the shogunate. I'm counting on you, Yugiri--

--! Ha ha! Certainly! I stake my honor as head of the Iga
ninja group on it.
Retiree-san, I've packed lots of dango for you to take home.
I also made plenty of wild strawberry dango. Please enjoy
Ah, thank you very much (Thump thump)

What's the matter, getting shy? You're a cute kid Perhaps
you've fallen for Omitsu-chan?

My apologies. My retainersno, the clerks at the shop will
be pleased. But Oei-dono... you have quite the allure. If I
were younger, I'd want to court a woman like you.

Ha ha! Next year I'll be in my unfazed forties. It's no use
giving me that look. If you like women so much, why don't
you go to the pleasure quarters, Retiree-san? (Smack smack)
(Eek! Oei-san is smacking His Lordship's back!?)
Ah! I'll carry the souvenirs for you, Retiree-sama!

Oh, when did Yugiri-chan get here? Karin is always in your
care. I'll give you some dango and daifuku to take home as
well.

No, it is I who am helped by Karin. I gratefully accept the
souvenirs. I will distribute them to my subordinates.
Then let us meet again. It was a great feast. Farewell.
Thank you for the meal! Oei-san, Omitsu-san
--The Shogun, Kanemaru, and Yugiri left the dango shop.

Retiree-san, even though you're retired, you brought a young
child with you. Is it because an employed head clerk is
taking over the shop? The clothes the child was wearing were
also very luxurious.

The souvenir dango were taken back by the hundred... perhaps
it's quite a large shop?

That's right. He must be a retiree from a very big shop,
don't you think? Ahaha...! (...I'm glad His Lordship's
identity wasn't discovered.)
